Commune in Guadeloupe, France

**Deshaies** (French pronunciation: [deɛ]; [Guadeloupean Creole](/Antillean_Creole): *Déhé*) is a [commune](/Commune_in_France) located in the [French](/France) [overseas region](/Overseas_region) and [department](/Overseas_department) of [Guadeloupe](/Guadeloupe), nestled within the [Lesser Antilles](/Lesser_Antilles) archipelago. It occupies a distinct position on the northwest coast of [Basse-Terre Island](/Basse-Terre_Island), a verdant and mountainous landmass that forms one of the two main islands of Guadeloupe.

